The primary use case is calculating the cosine similarity between two float arrays representing embedding vectors.  For example:

```java
float[] vector1 = {0.1f, 0.2f, 0.3f};
float[] vector2 = {0.4f, 0.5f, 0.6f};
double similarity = EmbeddingMath.cosineSimilarity(vector1, vector2);
```

It can also be used to calculate the dot product and norm of a vector:

```java
float[] vector = {0.1f, 0.2f, 0.3f};
float dotProduct = EmbeddingMath.dotProduct(vector, vector);
float norm = EmbeddingMath.norm(vector);
```

